<w:document xmlns:wpc="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingCanvas" xmlns:mo="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/mac/office/2008/main" xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" xmlns:mv="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:mac:vml" xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" xmlns:r="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/relationships" xmlns:m="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/officeDocument/2006/math" xmlns:v="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml" xmlns:wp14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingDrawing" xmlns:wp="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/drawingml/2006/wordprocessingDrawing" xmlns:w10="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word" xmlns:w="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/wordprocessingml/2006/main" xmlns:w14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordml" xmlns:wpg="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingGroup" xmlns:wpi="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingInk" xmlns:wne="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2006/wordml" xmlns:wps="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/word/2010/wordprocessingShape" mc:Ignorable="w14 wp14"><w:body><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading1"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>Smart Appointment Booking System</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>1. Project Overview</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>The Smart Appointment Booking System is a full-stack web application developed using Spring Boot and React. It allows users to book, manage, and track appointments efficiently while enabling admins to control slots and approvals. The system follows RESTful architecture and real-world business workflows.</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>2. Technology Stack</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>Frontend: React, Axios</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Backend: Spring Boot, Spring Data JPA</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Database: MySQL / PostgreSQL</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Security: Spring Security, JWT</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Notifications: Email and Phone-based reminders</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>3. Core Use Cases</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>1. User Registration and Login</w:t><w:br/><w:t>2. View Available Appointment Slots</w:t><w:br/><w:t>3. Book an Appointment</w:t><w:br/><w:t>4. Manage Appointments (View, Cancel, Reschedule)</w:t><w:br/><w:t>5. Admin Appointment and Slot Management</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>4. REST API Endpoints – Detailed Explanation</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p/><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>4.1 Authentication APIs</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>POST /api/auth/register</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Registers a new user into the system by storing user details securely.</w:t><w:br/><w:br/><w:t>POST /api/auth/login</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Authenticates the user and returns a JWT token for authorized access.</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>4.2 Slot Management APIs</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>GET /api/slots/available</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Returns all available appointment slots for a selected service and date.</w:t><w:br/><w:br/><w:t>POST /api/admin/slots</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Allows admin to add new available time slots for appointments.</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>4.3 Appointment APIs</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>POST /api/appointments/book</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Books an appointment for a user by assigning a selected slot and preventing double booking.</w:t><w:br/><w:br/><w:t>GET /api/appointments/my</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Fetches all appointments booked by the logged-in user.</w:t><w:br/><w:br/><w:t>PUT /api/appointments/cancel/{appointmentId}</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Cancels a booked appointment and frees the time slot.</w:t><w:br/><w:br/><w:t>PUT /api/appointments/reschedule/{appointmentId}</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Allows the user to reschedule an existing appointment to a new date or slot.</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>4.4 Admin APIs</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>GET /api/admin/appointments</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Fetches all appointments in the system for administrative review.</w:t><w:br/><w:br/><w:t>PUT /api/admin/appointments/{appointmentId}/status</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Allows admin to approve or reject appointment requests.</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>4.5 Notification &amp; Reminder APIs</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>POST /api/notifications/send</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Sends instant notifications via email and phone number.</w:t><w:br/><w:br/><w:t>POST /api/notifications/schedule</w:t><w:br/><w:t>Schedules reminder notifications 1 day before and 1 hour before the appointment time.</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>5. Reminder Workflow</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>When an appointment is booked, the system schedules two reminder jobs:</w:t><w:br/><w:t>- 24 hours before the appointment</w:t><w:br/><w:t>- 1 hour before the appointment</w:t><w:br/><w:t>These reminders are automatically sent via email and phone number.</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:pPr><w:pStyle w:val="Heading2"/></w:pPr><w:r><w:t>6. Conclusion</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p><w:r><w:t>This project demonstrates strong backend design, REST API implementation, role-based access control, and background task scheduling. It closely resembles a real-world appointment booking platform.</w:t><w:br/></w:r></w:p><w:sectPr w:rsidR="00FC693F" w:rsidRPr="0006063C" w:rsidSect="00034616"><w:pgSz w:w="12240" w:h="15840"/><w:pgMar w:top="1440" w:right="1800" w:bottom="1440" w:left="1800" w:header="720" w:footer="720" w:gutter="0"/><w:cols w:space="720"/><w:docGrid w:linePitch="360"/></w:sectPr></w:body></w:document>
